## What each alert means and what to do

### High API error rate
- Check: recent deploy (roll back if yes), bad input causing 500s, downstream service failure.
- First action: `<!-- AI: e.g. curl https://app.com/api/health -->`
- Runbook: [15-RUNBOOK-DEPLOY.md](./15-RUNBOOK-DEPLOY.md) — Rollback procedure
- Incident guide: [16-INCIDENT-RESPONSE.md](./16-INCIDENT-RESPONSE.md)

### Slow response time
- Check: slow DB queries (check slow query log), missing index, N+1 query, memory pressure.
- First action: Check DB slow query log.
- Runbook: <!-- AI: add link or steps -->

### DB connection pool exhausted
- Check: query taking too long, connection leak, spike in traffic.
- First action: Identify longest-running query. Kill if safe.
- Runbook: <!-- AI: add link or steps -->

### Brute-force login attempts
- Check: IP source, user accounts targeted.
- First action: Rate-limit or block source IP at edge.
- Runbook: <!-- AI: add link or steps -->

